FBIS4-61924 "drsov091_a_94017" FBIS-SOV-94-091 Daily Report 11 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Russian, French Paratroops To Hold Joint Exercises Russian, French Paratroops To Hold Joint Exercises LD1105104294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0924 GMT 11 May 94 LD1105104294 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Vlasov] [Text] Pskov May 11 TASS -- A delegation of French military officials arrived by plane here on Tuesday evening to familiarize themselves with the way of life of servicemen of the Pskov Airborne Infantry Division. They will visit the Division's quarters on Wednesday. Lieutenant Colonel Viktor Sorokin, chief of the Russian airborne infantry forces, is accompanying the French delegation. Sorokin and Major General Ivan Babichev, commander of the Pskov division in question, will do parachute jumps from an IL-76 assault aircraft on May 12. In June, 90 French paratroopers from an airborne infantry regiment stationed near the town of Castres are to come here to participate in a joint exercise with the Russian counterparts. They will stay here for ten days. Simultaneously, 90 Russian paratroopers from the Pskov Airborne Infantry Division will take part in a joint exercise in France.
